<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-07-22T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-07-22T02:00:00-05:00" n="181" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d181">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/13528: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-07-22T15:00:00+08:00">July 22, 1938—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>364. Shanghai’s 969, July 9, 2 p.m. Official report now received by mail
                            under seal of a letter signed by Morishima<note n="14" xml:id="d181fn14">Japanese Counselor of Embassy in China at Shanghai.</note> “for
                            Minister of War” the text of the statement quoted in Shanghai’s telegram
                            under reference.</p>
                        <p>Unless instructed otherwise I shall simply make formal acknowledgment of
                            this communication.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Shanghai.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>